<p>
    The Department of Computer Science and Engineering, Federal Institute of 
    Science and Technology (FISAT), Angamaly, Kerala, India, was establised in 
    the year 2002. The institution took an initiative to move towards free and
    Open Source software in the year 2008.  The campus currently has a single
    sign on set up based on Debian Lenny and handling around 1800 users.  The
    server is SUN Blade X-6250 and 1 TB storage.  The Central computing facility
    have an exclusive Debian lab primary used for teaching advanced C and Java
    programming for undergraduate and postgraduate students.  The primarily used 
    software are NFS, OpenLDAP, Samba, OpenJDK and Emacs.
</p>

<p>
    Debian was chosen for its 'free' nature and stability.
